  "text": "Given the importance of understanding gene induction during the initiation phase of negative selection, we treated N15 H-2 b mice with VSV8, and prepared RNA from FACSpuri®ed DP thymocytes for microarray analysis 0.5, 1 and 2 h after VSV8 treatment. At these time points, DP thymocyte apoptosis is not yet detected (Fig. 1A±C) , although nur77 and ikbns transcription is induced [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . RNA from FACS-sorted DP thymocytes of N15 H-2 d animals was used as a control. The N15 TCR does not recognize H-2 d class I molecules and therefore cannot be triggered in this background, so that neither positive nor negative selection occurs. Thus, thymocytes from N15 H-2 d mice express genes representative of DP cells not stimulated by pMHC and provide a clear gene expression baseline.",
